{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐξ-έδρα</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>hall</b> or <b>arcade furnished with recesses and seats,</b> in the gymnasia, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1449 (_anapaest meter_), 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Κωνεαζόμεναι” 10, “IPE” 12.182 (from Olbia), “IG” 12(3).1091 (from Melos), “BGU” 931.26 (1st c.AD), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; in the schools of Philosophers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.100M., 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 17.1.8, 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “de Finibus” 5.2.4, 1st c.BC: Vitruvius Scriptor de Architectura Latinus 5.11.2; in a private house, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 14.18. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>bench, seat,</b> in front of a house, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 4.19 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; any <b>public bench,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 13.4.5, 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 28.2 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>belvedere,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Nicolaus Damascenus Historicus “fragment” 1J. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>parlour</b> or <b>saloon,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Eze.40.44, 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Oralor” 3.5.17, “ND” 1.6.15, 1st c.BC: Vitruvius Scriptor de Architectura Latinus 6.7.3, 7.3.4, “POxy.” 912.13 (3rd c.AD)\">LXX+1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>the hall in Pompey's theatre at Rome,</b> where the Senate met, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Brutus” 14, 17. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7306","accentedUnicode":"ἐξέδρα","shortDef":"an inner chamber","mediumDef":"an inner chamber","stepGloss":"an inner chamber","stepTransliteration":"exedra","count":0,"_step_Type":"wor